  &lt;p class=&#34;wp-caption-text&#34;&gt;
    The Ajanta Caves. Maharashtra, India.
  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day 2, Entering Storyland at the Ajanta Caves:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We were entranced by the variety of paintings and stories depicted here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The thrill on sighting the mural of Padmapani holding a water lily, the delight on recognizing a Jataka tale depicted on the wall, the mixed feelings on spotting John Smith&amp;#8217;s name carved inside Cave 10&amp;#8230; it was a day to remember!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are some photographs from our second day at the remarkable Ajanta Caves, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Details about each cave are available at &lt;a title=&#34;Ajanta Caves&#34; href=&#34;http://ajantacaves.com/html/ajanta%20caves%20detailed.asp&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;AjantaCaves.com&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a title=&#34;Ajanta Caves - Wikipedia&#34; href=&#34;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ajanta_Caves&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Wikipedia&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

